Reasoning: The paper presents a new measure of causal influence between time series and leverages sequential prediction theory to estimate it. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the application of the proposed measure to stock market data suggests that the paper may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on causal inference and its use of Markov processes suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
